link: Vincenzo Librandi and T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000 (terms 1..680 from Vincenzo Librandi)
formula: Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(s - 4) / zeta(s - 3). The n-th term of the Dirichlet inverse is n^3 * A023900(n) = (-1)^omega(n) * a(n) / A003557(n), where omega=A001221. - _Álvar Ibeas_, Nov 24 2017
